<h1>Rates</h1>

<p>The &quot;Rates&quot; option of the &quot;Billing&quot; menu allows us to display and configure the rates per minute that are used to bill for the calls</p>

<div><img src="/images/help/reports/billing_rates.jpg" border="0"></div>
<div>Figure 1</div>
<br />

<h3>View, Edit and Delete</h3>

<p>The link View will take us to a screen where we will see the rate details.</p>

<div><img src="/images/help/reports/billing_rates_view.jpg" border="0"></div>
<div>Figure 2</div>
<br />

<p>To delete a rate, click on the “Delete” button.</p>

<p>You can also modify the values of the rate by clicking on the “Edit” button. The only values that can change are: Name, Rate and Rate Offset.</p>

<div><img src="/images/help/reports/billing_rates_edit.jpg" border="0"></div>
<div>Figure 3</div>
<br />

<h3>Create New Rate</h3>

<p>To add a new rate, click on the “Create New Rate” button. A form will be shown in which you will input the following fields:</p>

<div><img src="/images/help/reports/billing_rates_new.jpg" border="0"></div>
<div>Figure 4</div>
<br />

<table class="inline">
	<tr>
		<td>Prefix</td><td>The telephone prefix in which the rate will be applied.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>Name</td><td>Name of the rate</td>

	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>Rate</td><td>Monetary value of the Rate per minute</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>Rate Offset</td><td>Value of the connection.</td>
	</tr>

</table>
</body>
</html>
